@node "WhatIs" "What Is AutoSend?"

 AutoSend.br V2.1 has been specifically coded to use the excellent Miami by
 Holger Kruse.

 AutoSend.br will start Miami, go on-line, process all active Events, download
 waiting mail and or news, go off-line, parse and finally quit Miami. All these
 features are optional and are defined in command line arguments:

 AutoSend.br ONLINE/K,SEND/S,GET/K,LOGOFF/S,PARSE/S,LOGFILE/K,QUIT/S

 See @{" Usage " link Usage} for full details.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"

  @{b}Features@{ub}

  *  Uses the excellent Miami by Holger Kruse

  *  Uses Installer® script for installation and configuration

  *  AREXX script that can be:

     *   Executed from a cli

     *   Attached to a DOpus (or Toolmanager) button

     *   Selected from a menu item.

  *  Does not require Thor to be running.

  *  Has a user-configurable number of retries if mail/news servers are busy.

  *  Can be used with either a POP3 or SMTP systems (user-configurable)

  *  Has the following options

     *   Start Miami and/or go on-line

     *   Check for, and if found, process Active Events

     *   Get News

     *   Get Mail  (POP3 only)

     *   Get Both  (POP3 only)

     *   Log off   (Miami off-line)

     *   Parse waiting message packets

     *   Log all actions

     *   Quit Miami

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "System Requirements"

  @{b}Requirements@{ub}

  This script requires the following (not included in archive):

    rexxreqtools.library

    Miami (tested with V2.1a)

    Thor 2.x+ installed and correctly configured for TCP operations

  You also need to have AREXX up and running.  :^)

  The script has been tested on an A4000/040/40Mhz with OS3.1.

  It should work on Workbench 2.04/2.1/3.0.

  It will not work on Workbench 1.2/1.3.

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

@{b}  Installation@{ub}

   The installation and configuration of AutoSend.br is handled by an Installer®
   script.

   If you do not use it, AutoSend.br will not work (unless you create the
   configuration file by hand - not recommended).

   AutoSend.br will be copied to your Thor rexx/bbsread directory. Any existing
   file will be renamed AutoSend.br.old

   This guide file will be copied to the Thor Docs directory, overwriting any
   existing file.

   Please use the 'Help' button during the configuration process for an
   explanation of each option.


   @{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}

   In order to collect mail (POP3 only), it appears that your Login name must be
   configured in @{b}Mail (2)@{ub} of CfgTCP. If you have checked the 'Get from EMail
   address' box, your ISP may report "Unknown hostname" when you attempt to
   collect mail. Demon in the UK reports this error message.

   If you do receive the above error message, simply enter your Login name in
   the above configuration program. Remember to save the new settings.  ;)

   I've had a report from a user in the USA that this works OK with 'Get from EMail
   address' ticked, so I think it is very much ISP dependant.
   
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"

  @{b}Usage@{ub}

  The script can be used in a number of ways.

  The simplest way to to run it from a shell window with the following command
  line:

    rx (THORPath)rexx/AutoSend.br [<options>]

  Do not forget to use the actual path in place of (THORPath) in the command
  line.

  Another option would be to set up a button or menu item (using Tool Manager or
  DOpus 4/5) which would run the script when required. You should consult the
  relevant instructions/manuals for the program you use.

  If for any reason, Miami cannot go On-Line (i.e. you don't have Miami
  installed, your modem is switched off - or you press 'Cancel' during the
  on-line attempt - or for any other reason, a requester will pop up informing
  you of the problem. AutoSend.br will then exit.

  AutoSend V2.1 will report any errors in the command line arguments via
  requesters. If you use an incorrect option with the GET keyword, you will be
  advised accordingly. Likewise if you try to collect mail with an SMTP system.

  Furthermore, if you specify 'SEND' or 'GET' without specifying 'ONLINE', you
  be offered the option of going on-line.

  @{b}Template@{ub}

  AutoSend.br ONLINE/K,SEND/S,GET/K,LOGOFF/S,PARSE/S,LOGFILE/K,QUIT/S

  @{b}ONLINE@{ub}  - This option requires the keyword ONLINE and one of the
            following 2 options:

     @{b}HIDE@{ub}   Miami will be loaded (unless it already is) and then
            iconified.

     @{b}SHOW@{ub}   Miami will be loaded (unless it already is) but not
            iconified

  @{b}SEND@{ub}    - This will instruct AutoSend to check for any active Events,
            and if found will call SendTCP to process them.

  @{b}GET@{ub}     - This option requires the keyword GET and one of the following
            3 options (case insensitive):

     @{b}NEWS@{ub}   Calls GetTCP to fetch news from your configured (in Thor) News
            Server.

     @{b}MAIL@{ub}   Calls GetTCP to fetch mail from your configured (in Thor) Mail
            Server (POP3 ONLY).

     @{b}BOTH@{ub}   Will call GetTCP to fetch both news and mail as above. (POP3 only)

  @{b}LOGOFF@{ub}  - If specified, Miami will go Off-Line once everything else is complete.

  @{b}PARSE@{ub}     This option will parse waiting message packets into your Thor
            message base.

  @{b}LOGFILE@{ub} - This will enable the logging of all actions, whether successful or
            not. The keyword LOGFILE is required, followed by the full path and
            name of your log file. e.g. LOGFILE Logs:AutoSend.log

  @{b}QUIT@{ub}    - Will quit Miami.

@endnode

