@node "History" "History"

  @{b}History@{ub}

  V2.1 (17.6.97)    Added 2 options to the 'ONLINE' keyword. Miami can now be
                    started up and iconified by specifying 'HIDE'. Miami can be
                    un-inconified (if it's already in that state) by specifying
                    'SHOW'. See AmigaGuide doc for details. (Thanks to Audrey
                    McCalla for the suggestion)

                    Fixed a bug if the 'GET' keyword is not specified.
                    (Thanks to Audrey McCalla for the report)

                    Tidied up the code a little.

                    Changes to the Installer script - it no longer assumes the
                    presence of the 'Miami:' and 'Logs:' assigns.

  V2.0 (20.5.97)    A Miami specific version. Uses Installer® script for
                    installation and configuration.

                   'GET' keywords are no longer case sensitive

                    Errors in cmd line options are reported via requesters
  
  V1.0 (8.4.96)     First public release.
@endnode

